The course offers a holistic view of museum work in a social, cultural and political context. The course focuses on how to combine theoretical knowledge of museology flexibly with practice. The basics of documenting and describing museums, the basics of preservation, content development of exhibitions and communication are introduced. The main emphasis is on getting acquainted with the operation of museums in real situations.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give an overview of the research topics of museology as a subject; the history of museums; the role of museum institutions and their functioning in modern society.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student who has passed the subject:   Has an overview of museology as a specialty    knows the main trends in the history of museums    has an overview of the basics of modern museology    knows the principles of documenting and describing museums    is able to apply museological theories in museum activities and understands the role of museums in society   can find additional information in the field   values cultural heritage
